{"id":1732,"date":"2021-07-21T19:47:54","date_gmt":"2021-07-21T19:47:54","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/?page_id=1732"},"modified":"2023-01-13T13:11:18","modified_gmt":"2023-01-13T13:11:18","slug":"spontaneous-pneumothorax","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/spontaneous-pneumothorax\/","title":{"rendered":"Spontaneous Pneumothorax"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"1732\" class=\"elementor elementor-1732\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-237806f elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"237806f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-24d83c2\" data-id=\"24d83c2\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8178bf5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8178bf5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Cardiothoracic Surgery: Spontaneous Pneumothorax (PTX)<\/h1>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Spontaneous Pneumothorax<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-777e513 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"777e513\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-7824c76\" data-id=\"7824c76\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-795078e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"795078e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Definition<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Definition: Gas within the Pleural Space without Any External Event<\/li><li>Types:<ul><li><em>Primary<\/em>: No Underlying Clinical Lung Disease<\/li><li><em>Secondary<\/em>: From Underlying Clinical Lung Disease<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Risk Factors<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Male (3-6x Higher)<\/li><li>Smoking<\/li><li>Age:<ul><li>Primary \u2013 Generally Younger (10-30 Years)<\/li><li>Secondary \u2013 Generally Older (&gt; 55 Years)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Family History<\/li><li>Profession (Airline Pilot or Scuba-Diver)<\/li><li>Marfan Syndrome<\/li><li>Homocystinuria<\/li><li>Thoracic Endometriosis<\/li><li>Malnutrition<\/li><li>*Classic Patient with Primary Spontaneous Pneumothorax: Healthy, Thin, Tall, Young Male<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Association with COVID<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Uncommon Complication<ul><li>Incidence of Spontaneous PTX: 0.66%<\/li><li>Incidence of Cystic Changes in the Lung: 10%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Predominant Risk Factor: Mechanical Ventilation<\/li><li>Pathophysiology:<ul><li>Cytokine Storm \u2013 Hyperactive and Dysregulated Immune Response Causes a Hyperinflammatory form of ARDS<\/li><li>Thrombosis &amp; Microangiopathy<\/li><li>Pneumatocele May Be Due to Diffuse Alveolar Damage &amp; Necrosis of Airway Walls<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Causes<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Almost All are Due to <strong>Rupture of Subpleural Bleb\/Bullae<\/strong><ul><li>Cause of Both Primary &amp; Secondary Disease<\/li><li>Most Common Site: Right Upper Lobe Apex<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/pulmonary-cystic-lesions\/\">*See Cardiothoracic Surgery: Pulmonary Cystic Lesions<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Secondary Associations:<ul><li>COPD\/Emphysema \u2013 Most Common Cause of SSP (50-70%)<ul><li>Risk Correlates to Severity of Disease<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Interstitial Lung Disease<\/li><li>Malignancy<\/li><li>Tuberculosis (TB)<\/li><li>Sarcoidosis<\/li><li>Cystic Fibrosis<\/li><li><em>Catamenial Pneumothorax<\/em><ul><li>Pneumothorax Associated with <strong>Menstruation<\/strong><\/li><li><strong>Due to Thoracic Endometriosis<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Necrotizing Pneumonia<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Initial Imaging: Chest X-Ray (CXR)<\/li><li>Size:<ul><li>Small: \u2264 3 cm at Apex or \u2264 2 cm at Hilum<\/li><li>Large: &gt; 3 cm at Apex or &gt; 2 cm at Hilum<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Stable:<ul><li>Small: Observation with Supplemental Oxygen<ul><li>Resolves at <strong>1% Per Day<\/strong> without Treatment<\/li><li>Supplemental Oxygen: 6 L\/Minute for 6 Hours<ul><li>Increases Rate of Reabsorption Up to Six-Fold<\/li><li>Avoid Positive Pressure \u2013 Risk for Worsening<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Large: Catheter Aspiration or Chest Tube<ul><li>*Some Propose Conservative Management Even for Moderate-Large Size PTX if Asymptomatic (Debated)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Unstable: Chest Tube<ul><li>Smaller Diameter (\u2264 14 Fr) Generally Preferred<\/li><li>Generally Placed to Water-Seal Initially<ul><li>Consider Adding Suction (-10 to -20 cm H2O) if Fails<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Consider Needle Thoracostomy if Chest Tube Placement Will Cause Delay<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Complications<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Persistent Air Leak<\/em><ul><li><strong>Air Leak &gt; 4-5 Days<\/strong><\/li><li>Cerfolio Classification:<ul><li>Grade 1 (FE): During Forced Expiration Only (Cough)<\/li><li>Grade 2 (E): Only During Expiration<\/li><li>Grade 3 (I): Only During Inspiration<\/li><li>Grade 4 (C): Continuous During Both Inspiration &amp; Expiration<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Treatment: Surgery (VATS Thoracoscopy, Resection &amp; Mechanical Pleurodesis)<ul><li>If No Blebs are Seen \u2013 Still Preform an Apical Resection<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Recurrent Pneumothorax<\/em><ul><li>Risk: <strong>50-60%<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Tension Pneumothorax<\/em><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-79af0af\" data-id=\"79af0af\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-763250e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"763250e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13818 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Pneumothorax.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Pneumothorax.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Pneumothorax-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Pneumothorax-150x150.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Pneumothorax on CXR <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-efd41fe elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"efd41fe\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13819 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/PTX-CT.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/PTX-CT.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/PTX-CT-300x234.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Tension PTX on CT<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-74d60a2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"74d60a2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13808 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Lung-Bleb.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"192\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Lung-Bleb.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Lung-Bleb-300x115.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Pulmonary Blebs; (A) CT, (B) VATS <sup>2<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-dd23a1c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"dd23a1c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-conta